          <h4 class="font-semibold">Tiny bundle size</h4>
          <p>
            Front-end part of the app is 10x smaller than while using React.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold">Less traffic per interaction</h4>
          <p>
            Client sends light-weight notifications. Data transferring is well-optimized.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold">Low battery usage</h4>
          <p>
            Very little CPU activity when serving HTML content to a browser save battery from draining.
          </p>
        </div>
        <a href="https://docs.stimulusreflex.com/#build-the-next-twitter-in-just-9-minutes-or-less" class="flex items-center col-start-2 col-end-4 px-4 py-4 pr-5 space-x-4 font-semibold text-purple-600 border-2 border-purple-300 rounded-3xl">
          <%= image_tag "icons/play" %>
          <span class="flex items-center justify-between flex-grow">
            See video
            <%= image_tag "icons/arrow_circle_right" %>
          </span>
        </a>
      </div>
      <h3 class="mb-6 text-3xl font-semibold">
        Hot questions
      </h3>
      <div class="flex items-start mb-4">
        <span class="px-6 py-4 -mr-2 bg-gray-200 rounded-3xl">I’m working on a mature web app using React. Can I easily migrate to StimulusReflex?</span>
        <span class="px-6 py-4 mt-4 -ml-2 bg-purple-300 rounded-3xl">Unfortunately, you need to rewrite it. But you’ll reuse most of the code pieces.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-start mb-8 ml-20">
        <span class="px-6 py-4 -mr-2 bg-gray-200 rounded-3xl">I’m developing a real-time application with lots of interactions. Is StimulusReflex a good replacement for React?</span>
        <span class="px-6 py-4 mt-4 -ml-2 bg-purple-300 rounded-3xl">Sure it is! Use AnyCable library to get real-time updates.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-start ml-8">
        <span class="px-6 py-4 -mr-2 bg-gray-200 rounded-3xl">My app is mobile first. Can I write is using StimulusReflex?</span>
        <span class="px-6 py-4 mt-4 -ml-2 bg-purple-300 rounded-3xl">Yes, you can. StimulusReflex supports native mobile platforms.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pt-8 pb-20 mb-8 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto">
      <h2 class="mb-8 font-semibold text-purple-600 leading-20 text-7xl">
        Cost Saving
      </h2>
      <h3 class="mb-4 text-3xl font-semibold">
        Smaller team doing more
      </h3>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold">No need for high-skilled front-end</h4>
          <p>
            One full stack Rails developer can build a single codebase that serves web and native mobile.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold">Launch in days, not months</h4>
          <p>
            Less inter-team communication causes less delay and time to make an agreement.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold">Easy learning curve</h4>
          <p>
            Good documentations allow quick start and speeds up the development.
          </p>
        </div>
        <span class="col-span-3">
          <a href="https://docs.stimulusreflex.com/" class="flex items-center justify-between w-2/3 col-start-2 col-end-4 px-6 py-4 pr-5 mx-auto mt-4 font-semibold text-purple-600 border-2 border-purple-300 rounded-3xl">
            See how to start to develop with StimulusReflex
            <%= image_tag "icons/arrow_circle_right" %>
          </a>
        </span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container mx-auto">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-20">
        <div class="row-span-3">
          <%= image_tag "cable_ready_logo", class: "mx-auto" %>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-2">
          <h3 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-semibold">
            CableReady is ready to serve
          </h3>
        </div>
        <div class="col-start-2">
          <h4 class="font-semibold">Launch in days, not months</h4>
          <p>
